# An executed example page

This `.md` file is the **source**. `pyclawd docs compile` converts it to a notebook
via jupytext, `pyclawd docs run` executes and caches it, and nbsphinx renders the
result — including the output of the code cell below.

```python
import {{pkg}}

print("docs for {{name}}, version", {{pkg}}.__version__)
```

Edit this page, then `pyclawd docs build` — only changed notebooks re-execute
(jupyter-cache). `pyclawd docs timings` shows how long each took; `pyclawd docs
failures` flags any that raised.
